List all plugins that are currently active in the engine.

  Plugins are the unit of capability delivery. Each plugin registers
  one or more capabilities when it activates. If no plugins are active,
  the capability registry will be empty and no steps can execute.

  Plugins are loaded from JAR files via nexora.loadPlugin() or wired
  programmatically in your application code.

  Examples
  ────────
    nexora plugins
    nexora --config /etc/nexora/prod.json plugins
